'''Adesua Etomi''' (born 22 February)<ref>{{cite web|author1=Kayode Badmus|title=Adesua Etomi: Life of a ‘first class’ graduate turned screen diva as she celebrates another year|url=http://thenet.ng/2016/02/adesua-etomi-life-of-a-first-class-graduate-turned-screen-diva-as-she-celebrates-another-year/|publisher=''Nigerian Entertainment Today''|accessdate=29 May 2017|date=22 February 2016}}</ref> is a Nigerian actress. In 2014, she starred in her first feature film ''[[Knocking on Heaven's Door (2014 film)|Knocking On Heaven's Door]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pulse.ng/movies/adesua-etomi-5-movies-featuring-africas-best-actress-of-the-year-id4774601.html|title=Adesua Etomi: 5 movies featuring Africa's best actress of the year|first=Chidumga|last=Izuzu|publisher=}}</ref> She won the Best Actress in A Drama award at the [[2016 Africa Magic Viewers Choice Awards]] for her role in the 2015 romantic drama film ''[[Falling (film)|Falling]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bellanaija.com/2016/03/amvca2016-and-the-winners-are-genevieve-nnaji-stephanie-linus-folarin-falz-falana-funke-akindele-more-see-full-list/|title=#AMVCA2016 … and the Winners are Genevieve Nnaji, Stephanie Linus, Folarin ‘Falz’ Falana, Funke Akindele & More - See Full List|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://thenet.ng/2016/02/adesua-etomi-life-of-a-first-class-graduate-turned-screen-diva-as-she-celebrates-another-year/|title=Adesua Etomi: Life Of A 'first Class' Graduate Turned Screen Diva As She Celebrates Another Year - Nigerian Entertainment Today - Nigeria's Number 1 Entertainment Daily|date=22 February 2016|publisher=}}</ref>
== Early life and education == Tolulope Adesuwa Etomi was born in [[Owerri]], [[Imo State]], on 22 February.<ref name="dailymedia">{{Cite web |url=http://dailymedia.com.ng/biographyprofilehistory-of-nollywood-actress-adesua-etomi/ |title=Biography/Profile/History Of Nollywood Actress Adesua Etomi}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://stargist.com/entertainment/nigerian_celebrity/adesua-etomi-biography-adesua-etomi-wikipediaabout-adesua-etomiadesua-etomi-profileadesua-etomi/ |title=The Amazing Life of Adesua Etomi}}</ref> Several major editorials on Etomi state her birth year as 1988.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://dailymedia.com.ng/biographyprofilehistory-of-nollywood-actress-adesua-etomi/ |title=Biography/Profile/History Of Nollywood Actress Adesua Etomi |website=Daily Media}}</ref><ref name="punchng.com">{{Cite web |url=http://punchng.com/10-wonderful-things-to-know-about-adesua-etomi/ |title=10 wonderful things to know about Adesua Etomi |date=3 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.naij.com/1104448-adesua-etomi-biography.html |title=Adesua Etomi Biography |website=Naij}}</ref> However, in an interview published in January 2016, Etomi told ''Pulse Nigeria'' that she was 29 years old.<ref name="Pulse Nigeria">{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bwBptZt67NM |title=Full Interview: Nollywood Actress Adesua Etomi Chats With Pulse TV |publisher=Pulse Nigeria}}</ref> Furthermore, ''Answers Africa'' published an article in March 2016, stating that she was 30 years old.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://answersafrica.com/africas-best-actress-of-the-year-adesua-etomi.html |title=Africa's Best Actress of the Year; Adesua Etomi}}</ref> Her father is a soldier of [[Esan people|Esan]] descent, and her mother is an engineer of [[Yoruba people|Yoruba]] descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bellanaija.com/2015/02/birthday-turnup-nollywood-actress-adesua-etomi-celebrates-with-gideon-okeke-gbenro-ajibade-osas-ighodaro-linda-ejiofor-more/|title=Birthday Turnup! Nollywood Actress Adesua Etomi Celebrates with Gideon Okeke, Gbenro Ajibade, Osas Ighodaro, Linda Ejiofor & More|publisher=}}</ref> She is the youngest of three siblings.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://naijagists.com/nollywood-actress-adesua-etomi-im-esan-tribe-from-edo-state-my-mother-is-yoruba/|title=Nollywood Actress Adesua Etoni: I'm from Esan Tribe from Edo State, My Mother is Yoruba|website=Naija Gists|date=2 April 2016|accessdate =5 July 2016}}</ref> Etomi attended Corona School in [[Victoria Island, Lagos]], where she joined the drama club at the age of seven. Thereafter, she attended [[Queen's College, Lagos]] before moving to the [[United Kingdom]] at the age of 13 years old, and later obtained a [[diploma]] in "physical theatre, musical theatre and performing arts" from [[City College Coventry]] in 2004.<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://issuu.com/vanguardngr/docs/allure_05062016|publisher=Allure Magazine (Vanguard)|page=13|author=Yemisi Suleiman|title=AMAA Nominees 2016|date=5 June 2016|accessdate=8 October 2016}}</ref> After completing these courses in 2006 with triple distinctions, she studied drama and performance at the [[University of Wolverhampton]], graduating with [[First class degree|first-class honours]].<ref name="dailymedia"/>
== Career == Etomi's film credits include ''[[The Arbitration]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thenet.ng/2016/07/net-films-watch-o-c-ukeje-and-adesua-etomi-in-new-movie-the-arbitration/|title=NET Films: Watch O.C Ukeje and Adesua Etomi in new movie The Arbitration - Nigerian Entertainment Today - Nigeria's Top Website for News, Gossip, Comedy, Videos, Blogs, Events, Weddings, Nollywood, Celebs, Scoop and Games|date=28 July 2016|publisher=}}</ref> ''[[The Wedding Party (2016 film)|The Wedding Party]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.premiumtimesng.com/arts-entertainment/nollywood-nigeria/215114-wedding-party-banky-w-adesua-etomi.html|title=‘The Wedding Party’ of Banky W and Adesua Etomi - Premium Times Nigeria|date=11 November 2016|publisher=}}</ref> and ''[[Falling (film)|Falling]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thenet.ng/2015/08/falling-starring-desmond-elliot-and-adesua-etomi-to-hit-cinemas-next-month/|title=Nollywood Movie 'Falling' Which Stars Desmond Elliot And Adesua Etomi To Hit Cinemas In September - Nigerian Entertainment Today - Nigeria's Number 1 Entertainment Daily|date=13 August 2015|publisher=}}</ref> Her performance in ''Falling'' earned her the 2016 Africa Magic Viewers Choice Award for Best Actress In A Drama.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bellanaija.com/2015/09/falling-uduak-oguamanam/|title='Falling' to Premiere Tomorrow with Adesua Etomi, Blossom Chukwujekwu & Kunle Remi - Watch the Trailer|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.naij.com/tag/adesua-etomi-best-actress-2016-amvca.html|title=Adesua Etomi Best Actress 2016 AMVCA ▷ All News ▷ Naij.com|publisher=}}</ref> Other notable films she has appeared in include ''[[A Soldier's Story (2015 film)|A Soldier's Story]]'' (2015), ''[[Out of Luck (2015 film)|Out of Luck]]'' (2015),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bellanaija.com/2015/11/this-movie-trailer-is-a-must-watch-linda-ejiofor-femi-branch-jide-kosoko-tope-tedela-more-in-out-of-luck/|title=This Movie Trailer is a Must Watch! Linda Ejiofor, Femi Branch, Jide Kosoko, Tope Tedela & More in 'Out of Luck'|publisher=BellaNaija}}</ref> and ''Couple of Days'' (2016).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pulse.ng/movies/couple-of-days-watch-adesua-etomi-falz-enyinna-nwigwe-kiki-omeili-in-behind-the-scenes-id4545188.html|title="Couple of Days": Watch Adesua Etomi, Falz, Enyinna Nwigwe, Kiki Omeili in behind the scenes|first=Chidumga|last=Izuzu|publisher=}}</ref> Etomi played Shiela in the fourth and fifth seasons of ''[[Shuga (TV series)|Shuga]]'', a television soap opera about [[HIV/AIDS]] prevention.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mtvshuga.com/behind-the-scenes/series-4/adesua-etomi-talks-about-her-character-sheila-in-mtv-shuga-4/|title=MTV Shuga Behind the Scnenes - Adesua Etomi talks about her character Sheila in MTV Shuga 4|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mtvshuga.com/cast/sheila/|title=MTV Shuga character profile - Sheila|publisher=}}</ref> Etomi began starring as Amaka Obiora, an undercover police officer, in Yemisi Wada's crime series ''LasGidi Cops'', which debuted in June 2016 on television.<ref>{{cite web|title=Are You Ready for 'Lasgidi Cops: Special Crimes Unit'? Watch the Trailer of the Crime Series starring Joke Silva, Bimbo Akintola & More!|url=https://www.bellanaija.com/2016/06/are-you-ready-for-lasgidi-cops-special-crimes-unit-watch-the-trailer-of-the-crime-series-starring-joke-silva-bimbo-akintola-more/|publisher=BellaNaija|accessdate=12 May 2017|date=3 June 2016}}</ref>
==Personal life== She got engaged to [[Banky W.|Banky W]] in February 2017.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Jayne Augoye|title=It’s no movie, BankyW and actress Adesua Etomi announce engagement|url=http://www.premiumtimesng.com/arts-entertainment/nollywood-nigeria/230256-no-movie-bankyw-actress-adesua-etomi-announce-engagement.html|publisher=Premium Times|accessdate=3 May 2017|date=3 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thenet.ng/2017/05/see-photos-of-banky-w-and-adesua-etomi-at-their-introduction-ceremony/|title=See photos of Banky W and Adesua Etomi at their introduction ceremony|date=2017-05-06|work=Nigerian Entertainment Today|access-date=2017-05-25|language=en-GB}}</ref> They both got traditionally married on 19 November, Court Wedding on 20 November and on 25 November (2017) they had the White Wedding in [[Cape Town, South Africa]].<ref>{{cite web|title=#BAAD2017: Presents Banky W and Adesua Etomi’s White Wedding|url=https://theinformantspy.com/2017/11/baad2017-presents-banky-w-and-adesua-etomis-white-wedding/|website=The Informant Spy|accessdate=26 November 2017}}</ref>
