'''Laopan''' (''{{IPA|law˧pan˩ba˩}}'') is a [[Loloish language]] of northern [[Laos]]. It is spoken in [[Boun Tay District|Bun Tay District]], [[Phongsaly Province]], Laos, including in Phaophumuang village (Kingsada 1999).
