{{Other uses|Yesenia (disambiguation){{!}}Yesenia}} {{Infobox film | name = Yesenia | image = Yesenia film.jpg | director = [[Alfredo B. Crevenna]] | screenplay = {{Plainlist| * [[Julio Alejandro]] * [[Yolanda Vargas Dulché]] }} | story = [[Yolanda Vargas Dulché]] | starring = {{Plainlist| * [[Jacqueline Andere]] * [[Jorge Lavat]] }} | music = Sergio Guerrero | cinematography = José Ortiz Ramos | editing = Jorge Busto | released = {{Film date|df=yes|1971|9|11|Mexico}} | runtime = 121 minutes | country = Mexico | language = Spanish | budget = | gross = }}
'''''Yesenia''''' is a 1971 Mexican film directed by [[Alfredo B. Crevenna]] based on an original story by [[Yolanda Vargas Dulché]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Una gitana para tres actrices y un capitán para dos actores|url=http://www.eltelegrafo.com.ec/noticias/espectaculos/22/una-gitana-para-tres-actrices-y-un-capitan-para-dos-actores|website=eltelegrafo.com.ec|accessdate=4 November 2017|language=Spanish}}</ref> The film is starred [[Jacqueline Andere]] as the titular character, along to [[Jorge Lavat]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Jacqueline Andere será homenajeada en China por Yesenia|url=http://www.lametiche.com/noticia/jacqueline-andere-sera-homenajeada-en-china-por-yesenia/|website=lametiche.com|accessdate=4 November 2017|language=Spanish}}</ref>
== Plot == Yesenia ([[Jacqueline Andere]]) had grown up among gypsies but her mother was white. Obliged by the circumstances (and her parents), she felt the need to give it to an old gypsy woman whom Yesenia believed to be her grandmother. The love of a soldier, disappointment and other misunderstandings reveal the hidden truth.
